      	<div type="translation" xml:lang="fra" resp="part:sybr part:emfr">
      		
      		<p rend="stanza" n="1">
      			<l>Le poisson, la tortue, et le sanglier,</l>
      			<l>Et l’homme-lion, le nain,</l>
      			<l>Rāma, et Rāma, et Rāma,</l>
      			<l>Buddha, et Kalkin : tels sont les Dix.</l>
      		</p>
      		
      	</div>
      	
      	<div type="commentary"><!--Update!-->
      		<p>The three Rāmas are respectively Paraśurāma, Rāmacandra or Dāśaratha Rāma,  and Balarāma.</p>
      		<p>This verse is also found in the Southern recension of the Mahābhārata. See <bibl>
      				<ptr target="bib:Francis2014_02"/>
      				<citedRange unit="page">216-218</citedRange>.
      			</bibl>.</p>
      		
      	</div>
      	
